    <title>Counting linear extensions of restricted posets</title>
    <summary>  The classical 1991 result by Brightwell and Winkler states that the number of
linear extensions of a poset is #P-complete. We extend this result to posets
with certain restrictions. First, we prove that the number of linear extension
for posets of height two is #P-complete. Furthermore, we prove that this holds
for incidence posets of graphs. Finally, we prove that the number of linear
extensions for posets of dimension two is #P-complete.
</summary>
